<div id="review_2318728918" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2318728918" />
    <a title="Phyllis Depoe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/78839225-phyllis-depoe"><img alt="Phyllis Depoe" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2318728918?book_show_action=true">Mar 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Phyllis Depoe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Phyllis Depoe" href="/user/show/78839225-phyllis-depoe">Phyllis Depoe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2318728918" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18113635512308279523">A delightful collection of short stories depicting Chinese and North American immigrant culture which are easy to read, full of imagery and with the words lovingly crafted. The stories remind me of the important things in life such as love, family, especially education, and values such as democracy and freedom particularly for women. It is very relevant today as it reminds us of the atrocities and harm that societies can inflict upon people in the name of progress by autocratic rulers such as Ma</span>
  <span id="freeText18113635512308279523" style="display:none">A delightful collection of short stories depicting Chinese and North American immigrant culture which are easy to read, full of imagery and with the words lovingly crafted. The stories remind me of the important things in life such as love, family, especially education, and values such as democracy and freedom particularly for women. It is very relevant today as it reminds us of the atrocities and harm that societies can inflict upon people in the name of progress by autocratic rulers such as Mao during the Cultural Revolution. The female characters finding themselves in difficult situations such as betrayal or lost love show strength and fortitude in becoming independent. It reminds us of the progress and opportunities for women especially in becoming educated. The author makes intelligent use of dream and memory sequences as her characters reveal their stories. Tales of nature are interspersed throughout the book and the last tale is about conserving our environment. The imagery of food is an integral theme woven throughout and sustains the characters in their quest for freedom. The stories are a mixture of Chinese proverbs, poetry and words that flow like musical notes. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18113635512308279523" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


