<div id="review_4205008376" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4205008376" />
    <a title="Maria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21564357-maria"><img alt="Maria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1484942900p2/21564357.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4205008376?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria" href="/user/show/21564357-maria">Maria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook " href="/book/show/58878469-butterfly-tears">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21564357-maria?shelf=purchased-in-2021">purchased-in-2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4205008376" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13425140752573922563">NOTE: I won a free eBook copy of this book in PDF format from LibraryThing&apos;s Member Giveaway.<br/><br/>I have long been interested in stories about Asia&apos;s human history, so this collection piqued my interest. Roy gives readers an insider&apos;s perspective of China&apos;s &quot;Cultural Revolution&quot; and how it impacted the lives of emerging adults and the people they loved. While many of the stories involve the struggles of being Chinese in North America, others (namely, &quot;Noodles&quot; and &quot;Life Insurance&quot;) are gently humorou</span>
  <span id="freeText13425140752573922563" style="display:none">NOTE: I won a free eBook copy of this book in PDF format from LibraryThing's Member Giveaway.<br /><br />I have long been interested in stories about Asia's human history, so this collection piqued my interest. Roy gives readers an insider's perspective of China's "Cultural Revolution" and how it impacted the lives of emerging adults and the people they loved. While many of the stories involve the struggles of being Chinese in North America, others (namely, "Noodles" and "Life Insurance") are gently humorous. As I read, I felt a sense of overlap between the stories: "Herbs" bleeds into "A Mandarin Duck," and "A Mandarin Duck" into "Noodles." Through the running threads connecting each of these stories, Roy explores issues impacting her Chinese-born protagonists' identity, feminism, and sexuality.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13425140752573922563" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


