<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer7563516310888373188">Born in China, Zoë S. Roy, an avid reader even during the Cultural Revolution, writes literary fiction with a focus on women’s cross-cultural experiences. She holds an MEd in Adult Education and an MA in Atlantic Canada Studies from the University of New Brunswick and Saint Mary’s University. She is a former teacher and lives in Toronto.<br/>Being a contributor to Wikipedia, she&apos;s created pages, such a</span>
  <span id="freeText7563516310888373188" style="display:none">Born in China, Zoë S. Roy, an avid reader even during the Cultural Revolution, writes literary fiction with a focus on women’s cross-cultural experiences. She holds an MEd in Adult Education and an MA in Atlantic Canada Studies from the University of New Brunswick and Saint Mary’s University. She is a former teacher and lives in Toronto.<br />Being a contributor to Wikipedia, she's created pages, such as Inanna Publications, Reginald C. Stuart, Amanda K. Hale, Eleanor Ty, and Peter Thomas McGuigan.</span>
